'''''Star Wars 31: Return to Tatooine''''' is the thirty-first issue in the [[1977]] [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] series of comics.

==Plot summary==
[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] returns to [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] for the first time since leaving with [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]]. His mission is to recruit [[CR90 corvette/Legends|blockade runner]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] to help the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] evacuate their base on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]]. However, while he is there he finds some clues to a secret plan of the [[House of Tagge/Legends|House of Tagge]] working with the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]], but not enough to find out exactly what they are up to. He goes to [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] to continue his original mission, and reunites with [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] in the same [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] where they had originally met [[Standard month/Legends|months]] earlier. But the celebration is cut short as [[Laze Loneozner/Legends|Fixer]] arrives to warn Luke that the Empire is aware that the young Rebel is on Tatooine and actively searching for him.

